
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Employees' Goal Orientations, the Quality of Leader-Member Exchange, and the Outcomes of Job Performance and Job Satisfaction
AU  - Janssen, Onne
AU  - Van Yperen, Nico W.
Y1  - 2004/06/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/20159587
DO  - 10.5465/20159587
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 368
EP  - 384
VL  - 47
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - As hypothesized, data from 170 employees of a Dutch firm showed that the quality of leader-member exchange mediated positive relationships between a mastery orientation and leader-rated in-role job performance, leader-rated innovative job performance, and job satisfaction. In contrast, a performance orientation was negatively related or unrelated to those outcomes. These findings suggest that employees with stronger mastery orientations are more effective on the job because they tend to establish higher-quality exchanges with their supervisors.
AB  - As hypothesized, data from 170 employees of a Dutch firm showed that the quality of leader-member exchange mediated positive relationships between a mastery orientation and leader-rated in-role job performance, leader-rated innovative job performance, and job satisfaction. In contrast, a performance orientation was negatively related or unrelated to those outcomes. These findings suggest that employees with stronger mastery orientations are more effective on the job because they tend to establish higher-quality exchanges with their supervisors.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/20159587
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/20159587
Y2  - 2026/04/24
