TY  - JOUR
T1  - You Paid for the Skills, Now Keep Them: Tuition Reimbursement and Voluntary Turnover
AU  - Benson, George S.
AU  - Finegold, David
AU  - Mohrman, Susan Albers
Y1  - 2004/06/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/20159584
DO  - 10.5465/20159584
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 315
EP  - 331
VL  - 47
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Does investing in employees' marketable skills reduce turnover? This study uses insights from human capital theory to explain how general skill development and promotion relate to voluntary turnover. Data from 9,439 salaried employees of a large manufacturer show that participation in tuition reimbursement reduces turnover while employees are in school. Voluntary turnover increases when individuals earn graduate degrees but is significantly reduced if they are subsequently promoted.
AB  - Does investing in employees' marketable skills reduce turnover? This study uses insights from human capital theory to explain how general skill development and promotion relate to voluntary turnover. Data from 9,439 salaried employees of a large manufacturer show that participation in tuition reimbursement reduces turnover while employees are in school. Voluntary turnover increases when individuals earn graduate degrees but is significantly reduced if they are subsequently promoted.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/20159584
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/20159584
Y2  - 2026/04/24
